    What is Abdul Kalam famous for?
    He was known as the 'Missile Man of India' for his work in the development of ballistic missile technology. From 1992 to 1999, Kalam was the Chief Scientific Adviser to the Prime Minister and the Secretary of the DRDO. Kalam was the Chief Project Coordinator during the Pokhran II tests.

    Does Kalam believe in God?
